content.text:
The bug was that selecting an already selected card in the Card Browser (in multi-select mode) would not unselect it. This was caused by the `onItemClickListener` in `CardBrowser.kt` calling `viewModel.selectRowAtPosition(position)`, which only *adds* the card to the selection set, instead of toggling it.

I fixed this by changing the call to `viewModel.toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position)`, which correctly adds or removes the card from the selection set based on its current state.

### Code Changes

In `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/CardBrowser.kt`:

```kotlin
<<<<
                // click on whole cell triggers select
                val cb = view!!.findViewById<CheckBox>(R.id.card_checkbox)
                cb.toggle()
                viewModel.selectRowAtPosition(position)
            } else {
====
                // click on whole cell triggers select
                val cb = view!!.findViewById<CheckBox>(R.id.card_checkbox)
                cb.toggle()
                viewModel.toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position)
            } else {
>>>>
```

This ensures that clicking a selected card deselects it, and clicking an unselected card selects it, as expected. The UI updates correctly because the ViewModel emits a state change which triggers `notifyDataSetChanged` on the adapter, rebinding the views with the correct checkbox state.

